==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Electro-magnetic
<hw>E*lec`tro-mag*net"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or
pertaining to <er>electromagnetism</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Electro-magnetic engine</b></col>, <cd>an engine in which
the motive force is electro-magnetism.</cd> -- <col><b>Electro-magnetic
theory of light</b></col> <fld>(Physics)</fld>, <cd>a theory of light
which makes it consist in the rapid alternation of transient electric
currents moving transversely to the direction of the ray.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Electro-magnetism</ent>⟦br⟧
